To fix this issue, you need to wait for the new window to finish loading before you can modify its content. One way to do this is to use the `onload` event of the `window` object to execute your code. Here's how you can modify your code to ensure that the new window is fully loaded before appending the script tag:

```
var newWindow = window.open('https://www.google.com/');

newWindow.onload = function() {
  newWindow.document.write("hi");

  var script = newWindow.document.createElement('script');
  script.src = 'js/myScript.js';
  newWindow.document.head.appendChild(script);
};
```

With this code, the `onload` function is executed when the new window is done loading. Then you can safely modify the `document` object of the new window and append a new `script` tag.

